CBRE Saskatchewan is pleased to offer 42.37 acres of highway fronting land adjacent to the bustling city of Warman, SK. As Saskatchewans newest and fastest growing city, Warman boasts a robust, young population of over 17 500 residents. Located just 10 kilometers north of Saskatoon, Warman continues to bean attractive location for both commercial and residential development. Services to the site include a water and sewer pipe running along the east side of the property, with power serviced to the site as well. Many great local bakeries, coffee shops, and restaurants are located within a few kilometers of the property.

Nestled in a picturesque bend of the South Saskatchewan River, less than five kilometers north of the city of Saskatoon, Saskatchewan, RiverBend is a community with an innovative design which aspires to meet the basic principles of environmental and social sustainability. It is a complete community which includes acres of intriguing parks and green spaces, innovative public recreation facilities, opportunity for local businesses and community organizations and a variety of housing options meant to accommodate the dreams of a wide range of homebuyers.

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text: CBRE is pleased to offer for sale a total of  5.05 acres for multifamily residential uses located in The Meadows, a 420 acre master-planned community, nestled in the Rosewood neighborhood of Saskatoon, SK. When completed, The Meadows will feature 2,200+ new homes and 65 acres of parks, ponds and pathways. Within the Meadows, lies the Meadows Market, a retail power centre with Costco, boutiques, restaurants, and many more amenities. Overall, the site is well situated within Saskatoon and is a short 7 minute drive to the city center.

CBRE is pleased to offer 160 acres located on the East side Range Road 3063 north of 33rd Street West in the Rural Municipality of Corman Park, Saskatchewan. The land is currently leased to a farmer for a grain growing operation and located within the Saskatoon Planning District, an area jointly managed by the R. M. of Corman Park and the City of Saskatoon. It is expected that at some date in the future the boundary of the City of Saskatoon may be extended to include this quarter section.
